1 (4) The board shall retain medical personnel to advise it in assessing the nature and extent of
2 disabling conditions while reviewing claims for disability retirement.
3 (5) The disability retirement benefit paid to a member of the defined benefit plan must be
4 converted to a service retirement benefit, without recalculation of the monthly benefit amount, when the
5 member has attained normal retirement age. The board shall notify the member in writing as to the change in
6 status The disability retirement benefit paid to a member of the defined benefit plans provided for in Title 19,
7 chapters 9 and 13, remains a disability retirement benefit when the member attains normal retirement age, but
8 the disability retirement benefit is no longer subject to a medical examination of the member."
9
10 Section 2. Section 19-9-903, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "19-9-903. Amount of disability retirement benefit -- continuation of benefit after death of
12 member. (1) A member who becomes disabled:
13 (a) before completing 20 years of membership service must receive a disability retirement benefit
14 equal to one-half the member's final average compensation; or
15 (b) after completing 20 years or more of membership service must receive a disability retirement
16 benefit equal to 2.5% of the member's final average compensation for each year of service credit.
17 (2) A member who becomes disabled as a direct result of the member's service in the line of duty:
18 (a) before completing 20 years of membership service must receive a line of duty disability
19 retirement benefit equal to one-half of the member's final average compensation; or
20 (b) after completing 20 years or more of membership service must receive a line of duty disability
21 retirement benefit equal to 2.5% of the member's final average compensation for each year of service credit.
22 (2)(3) Upon the death of a member receiving a disability retirement benefit under this section, the
23 member's surviving spouse or dependent child is eligible for benefits as provided in 19-9-804."
24
